interactionTemplates:
Two types of recipients require different event structures:
- Services/agents (e.g., persistence, robot): Send operations via content.tasks. See Event Tasks section.
- Human participants (e.g., participant0, $groupName): Send messages via advice with an interaction template.

For participants, ALWAYS include advice with at least a text element in the interaction template. A publish without advice (or with only title/description and no advice) is unlikely to produce any visible output for the participant.

Advice structure:
- advice.eventType (string, OPTIONAL): The response event type. When collecting input from the participant, this MUST be 'org.wt.client.tell'. Omit for display-only messages (notifications, alerts, status updates, informational messages where no response is expected).
- advice.title (string, optional): Suggested title for the response.
- advice.template:
  - name (string, required): Template name.
  - interactions (array, required): Array of InteractionModel objects.
    - interaction.content (array): Array of ElementModel objects.

Element types — choose based on communication intent:
- text: Display readable information to the participant. Use for all notifications, status updates, instructions, and informational messages.
  {"text": {"value": "message text or $xpr(...)"}}
- input: Collect a response value from the participant. Requires advice.eventType = 'org.wt.client.tell'.
  {"input": {"type": "boolean|numeric|text|nominal", "name": "field_name", "display": "Prompt text", ...}}
- map: Display a location map with labeled markers.
  {"map": {"locations": [{"name": "str", "latitude": "str", "longitude": "str", "display": "uri"}]}}
- image: Display an image.
  {"image": {"uri": "string", "width": number, "height": number}}
- video: Display a video stream or clip.
  {"video": {"uri": "string|$xpr(...)"}}
- group: Nest multiple elements together.
  {"group": {"items": [...elements...]}}

Multiple elements: A single interaction can contain any combination of elements (text + map, text + video, text + input, etc.).

Input types (for input elements):
- boolean: {"type": "boolean", "name": "field_name", "display": "Prompt text", "set": [{"display": "Yes", "value": true}, {"display": "No", "value": false}]}
- numeric: {"type": "numeric", "name": "field_name", "display": "Prompt text"}
- text: {"type": "text", "name": "field_name", "display": "Prompt text"}
- nominal: {"type": "nominal", "name": "field_name", "display": "Prompt text", "set": [{"display": "Option A", "value": "a"}, {"display": "Option B", "value": "b"}], "multiple": false}

Accessing responses: In the reaction that handles the participant's response, filter on $event.type = 'org.wt.client.tell'. The input values are in the event's values payload — use $valueNamed('field_name') where field_name matches the input's name property.

Example 1 — Display-only notification (no response needed, omit eventType):
{"template": {"name": "notification", "interactions": [{"interaction": {"content": [{"text": {"value": "$xpr('Robot deployed at ' & $valueNamed('latitude') & ', ' & $valueNamed('longitude'))"}}]}}]}}

Example 2 — Approval with input (response needed, eventType must be org.wt.client.tell):
{"eventType": "org.wt.client.tell", "template": {"name": "approval_form", "interactions": [{"interaction": {"content": [{"text": {"value": "Please review this request"}}, {"input": {"type": "boolean", "name": "approved", "display": "Approve?", "set": [{"display": "Yes", "value": true}, {"display": "No", "value": false}]}}]}}]}}

Example 3 — Rich notification with text and map (display-only, no eventType):
{"template": {"name": "location_alert", "interactions": [{"interaction": {"content": [{"text": {"value": "$xpr('Detection at confidence ' & $string($valueNamed('confidence'))"}}, {"map": {"locations": [{"name": "Detected Location", "latitude": "$xpr($valueNamed('latitude'))", "longitude": "$xpr($valueNamed('longitude'))", "display": "detection"}]}}]}}]}}
